pageContext.claim: “As I have long said, @Pfizer and the others would only announce a Vaccine after the Election, because they didn't have the courage to do it before. Likewise, the @US_FDA should have announced it earlier, not for political purposes, but for saving lives!”
pageContext.analysis: There is no evidence that the development of a vaccine was delayed for political reasons or because of the election. Ironically, the process went faster than expected because the U.S. caseload was so high.
